ODM leader Raila Odinga toured Busia on Sunday. He first attended a church service at Lwanya Catholic Church in Matayos and then headed for Bukalama Resort, where he will meet Busia leaders and ODM delegates. In the afternoon, is expected to hold a rally at Busia stadium to popularise BBI. He was accompanied by Busia Governor Sospeter Ojaamong, Deputy Governor Moses Mulomi and MPs Raphael Wanjala of Budalang'i, Woman Rep Florence Mutua, Geoffrey Odanga of Matayos, Caleb Amisi of Saboti, Samuel Atandi of Alego Usonga and Wilberforce Mudenyo (Funyula). Siaya Governor Cornel Rasanga, former Funyula MP Paul Otuoma were also in attendance. More follows...